WEBVTT

00:19.353 --> 00:21.469
[ALL CHANTING INCANTATION]

00:30.906 --> 00:33.397
JASON:
Jessica!

00:35.702 --> 00:36.782
No.

00:38.872 --> 00:42.035
-Argh! No! No!
JESSICA: Ah!

00:42.459 --> 00:46.327
[ALL CHANTING INCANTATION]

00:46.797 --> 00:48.207
[JESSICA GRUNTING]

00:49.383 --> 00:51.214
[JESSICA GROWLS]

00:52.135 --> 00:54.171
[JASON SCREAMING]

02:25.145 --> 02:27.932
[ALL CHANTING INCANTATION]

02:31.693 --> 02:33.433
[JASON SCREAMING]

02:43.163 --> 02:46.496
-JeSSica.
-Oh, my God.

02:47.501 --> 02:48.911
You just saved my life.

02:56.718 --> 02:57.833
I'm sorry.

03:06.561 --> 03:08.768
BILL:
Jessica!

03:09.356 --> 03:10.892
Jessica!

03:11.066 --> 03:13.682
Jessica!

03:13.860 --> 03:15.521
Jessica.

03:15.737 --> 03:17.773
[SOBBING]

03:21.368 --> 03:23.404
Oh, no. Bucky.

03:23.578 --> 03:26.069
-I got her.
-Thank you.

03:27.958 --> 03:29.949
JESSICA:
Did I do that?

03:30.168 --> 03:31.749
You were not yourself.

03:31.962 --> 03:34.453
-His family?
BILL: They will be well compensated.

03:35.048 --> 03:38.381
All the guards know the dangers
inherent in theirjob.

03:39.094 --> 03:40.800
But I knew his little girl.

03:40.971 --> 03:43.383
Jessica, you were spellbound.

03:43.557 --> 03:46.048
You did not kill Bucky.

03:46.226 --> 03:48.217
The witch Antonia did.

03:50.313 --> 03:52.895
We need to get her back in the cell.

03:53.066 --> 03:55.227
They may have temporarily
broken the spell...

03:55.402 --> 03:57.814
...in the hope that we drop our guard.

03:57.988 --> 04:00.104
We will not be safe until nightfall.

04:01.241 --> 04:02.981
He's right.

04:04.703 --> 04:06.819
I don't wanna die.

04:06.997 --> 04:09.363
I don't want you to die either.

04:09.541 --> 04:11.031
Come on.

04:13.044 --> 04:14.580
I gotcha.

04:15.046 --> 04:17.173
[JESSICA GROANING]

04:24.014 --> 04:26.756
I'm so sorry, Jess.

04:27.768 --> 04:29.724
I know it hurts.

04:30.771 --> 04:33.604
Please make sure it is secure.

04:34.566 --> 04:37.603
BILL: I clearly underestimated
her strength earlier.

04:37.819 --> 04:39.400
[GROANING]

04:39.738 --> 04:42.855
Better for a little pain now
than to be able to escape again...

04:43.033 --> 04:45.445
...if the necromancer resumes
her sorcery.

04:46.119 --> 04:50.954
Think good things.
Hot summer day, barbecuing.

04:53.460 --> 04:54.791
No.

04:54.961 --> 04:57.953
Good things a vampire would think of.

04:58.381 --> 05:01.293
The moon. Never getting cold.

05:01.468 --> 05:03.629
-Tru Blood.
-Jason.

05:03.804 --> 05:06.420
-Yep?
-We will be indebted to you forever...

05:06.598 --> 05:11.638
...but right now Jessica and I need to get
some rest, if only for a few minutes.

05:11.812 --> 05:13.677
We need to regain our strength.

05:18.485 --> 05:19.565
All right.

05:25.617 --> 05:31.237
I realize, as a law-enforcement officer,
that you might feel the need to report this...

05:31.414 --> 05:33.666
...but vampires killing humans
is not something...

05:33.834 --> 05:36.041
...that I can afford to have documented.

05:36.211 --> 05:37.371
Not to mention....

05:45.470 --> 05:46.971
Yeah.

05:48.890 --> 05:51.097
It's probably for the best...

05:52.018 --> 05:54.304
...that I don't report that.

05:55.438 --> 05:58.521
It's also probably for the best
that nobody has to know anything...

05:58.692 --> 06:00.853
...about your boy that I shot outside.

06:02.195 --> 06:03.526
In the shoulder.

06:03.905 --> 06:04.940
Unquestionably.

06:08.118 --> 06:10.860
You won't wanna make
any sudden movements when they enter.

06:14.916 --> 06:15.951
MAN 1: Freeze!
MAN 2: Stand down.

06:16.126 --> 06:18.788
MAN 1: Hands up where we can see them.
MAN 2: Got a man down.

06:20.046 --> 06:21.297
MARCUS:
Now...

06:21.464 --> 06:26.128
...my source didn't know why the vampires
and witches would want a war...

06:26.303 --> 06:27.713
...or who started it.

06:27.888 --> 06:30.630
And, personally, I don't fucking care.

06:31.725 --> 06:33.556
But here's what I think.

06:33.727 --> 06:38.721
Those witches are fucking idiots
for getting mixed up in vampire shit.

06:38.899 --> 06:40.480
Did you tell him?

06:40.650 --> 06:42.106
Of course not.

06:42.277 --> 06:45.144
MARCUS:
Because those dead fuckers are hardcore.

06:45.322 --> 06:48.985
They will kill you and not blink an eye.

06:49.159 --> 06:51.070
Even we are no match for them.

06:51.578 --> 06:53.068
Yo, speak for yourself.

06:53.246 --> 06:56.579
Yo, don't be a fucking moron.

06:56.750 --> 06:57.739
CROWD: Heh, heh.
MAN 1: Dumb-ass.

06:57.918 --> 07:00.751
You think a vampire wouldn't rip you
to pieces in a heartbeat?

07:00.921 --> 07:03.128
MAN 2: Yeah.
-I'd fucking put up a fight at least.

07:03.298 --> 07:05.664
No, you wouldn't. You would be dead.

07:05.842 --> 07:07.082
MAN 2:
Wouldn't fight nothing.

07:07.260 --> 07:09.842
It might hurt our pride to admit that...

07:10.013 --> 07:13.176
...but it'll save our lives
and the lives of this pack...

07:13.350 --> 07:18.936
...which is why
this pack will stay the fuck out of it.

07:19.689 --> 07:22.476
Unless you want to go it
on your own, hotdog.

07:22.692 --> 07:25.104
CROWD: Ha, ha, ha.
MAN 3: I'd like to see that.

07:38.750 --> 07:41.958
Luna, it's me.

07:44.214 --> 07:45.203
Which one of you?

07:45.799 --> 07:49.291
The one who just kicked
my little brother out of my life for good.

07:49.469 --> 07:51.300
Is that supposed to make me feel better?

07:51.471 --> 07:55.305
It's not supposed to make you feel
anything. I just wanted to let you know.

08:01.648 --> 08:04.811
I wish you would have told me
your brother was a skin walker.

08:04.985 --> 08:07.852
-Well, I wish I would have known.
-Who did--? Who did he--?

08:08.029 --> 08:09.530
Mother and father.

08:09.739 --> 08:11.991
I'm not gonna lie to you.
They deserved it.

08:12.158 --> 08:14.240
They abused him his whole life.

08:14.411 --> 08:16.026
They fought him in dogfights.

08:16.246 --> 08:17.486
-Oh, my God.
-Yeah.

08:17.664 --> 08:19.950
And you wanna know something else?

08:20.875 --> 08:24.493
I can forgive him for killing our folks...

08:24.921 --> 08:28.379
...but I can't forgive him
for what he did to you. I can't.

08:30.343 --> 08:33.210
-Sam.
-Hey, Emma.

08:33.388 --> 08:36.972
My Barbie who's a pony likes you,
but my Barbie who's a cat doesn't like you.

08:37.142 --> 08:39.098
-She doesn't like anybody.
-Oh.

08:39.269 --> 08:42.682
You should hear how cat Barbie feels
about yours truly.

08:42.897 --> 08:44.182
[CHUCKLES]

08:44.357 --> 08:48.566
-I could use some help making dinner.
-No. Sam's playing with me.

08:48.778 --> 08:52.771
-And by help, I mean playing with Emma.
-Nothing would make me happier.

08:54.492 --> 08:58.701
Hey, Emma, let's see if we can get
cat Barbie to like me.

08:58.872 --> 09:02.035
You can try, but she won't.

09:06.212 --> 09:08.874
Yank it off. It's better.

09:10.383 --> 09:14.547
Oh. Well, won't it pull some of you off
with it?

09:14.721 --> 09:17.554
Yeah, but that's okay.

09:18.308 --> 09:23.428
It doesn't hurt as much as the silver,
and it heals faster.

09:25.231 --> 09:27.768
[SCREAMING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

09:28.651 --> 09:30.152
Thank you.

09:30.320 --> 09:32.902
-But you said it would heal faster.
-Ugh!

09:34.074 --> 09:35.189
Ugh!

09:36.159 --> 09:39.401
Yeah, I'm just realizing
I haven't fed since I--

09:39.579 --> 09:41.160
Since my fairy godmother?

09:41.331 --> 09:42.912
Right.

09:43.333 --> 09:45.449
[PANTING]

09:50.215 --> 09:51.796
[GRUNTS]

09:52.509 --> 09:53.919
You want a Tru Blood?

09:54.094 --> 09:56.756
Oh, no, a Tru Blood
isn't gonna help with this.

09:58.056 --> 10:00.593
I just need a rest.

10:01.267 --> 10:02.768
You need to feed.

10:02.936 --> 10:04.472
Well, there is no one.

10:07.023 --> 10:08.138
There's me.

10:14.114 --> 10:16.355
Please don't say this
if you don't mean it.

10:17.367 --> 10:18.447
I do mean it.

10:21.538 --> 10:24.621
-Now, you know my blood's special, like--
-Like the fairy goddess.

10:24.791 --> 10:29.876
Just a fraction of that,
and I'm trusting you not to lose control.

10:30.880 --> 10:36.125
Take something silver,
hold it in your hand...

10:36.302 --> 10:38.463
...and silver me
should I do anything unwanted.

10:47.272 --> 10:48.728
I'm trusting you, Eric.

10:48.898 --> 10:51.389
I won't betray you.

10:52.152 --> 10:53.141
Ever.

10:55.155 --> 10:58.318
I may remind you of that someday.

11:14.632 --> 11:16.372
[SOOKIE GRUNTS]

11:27.937 --> 11:29.438
[ERIC GRUNTS]

11:35.945 --> 11:37.060
[GRUNTS]

11:44.954 --> 11:46.535
But I'm not injured.

11:46.706 --> 11:48.992
We will be one.

12:00.136 --> 12:01.876
[GRUNTING]

12:13.983 --> 12:15.894
MAN 1 [ON TV]:
What is this? This is very cool.

12:16.069 --> 12:19.732
MAN 2: This is a 10th-century Viking skull,
and it presumably belonged to a....

12:19.906 --> 12:20.986
Oh my God.

12:22.492 --> 12:25.450
-Where you been? I've been worried sick.
-I know. Ijust had to--

12:25.620 --> 12:31.581
I had this strange feeling,
like I thought I lost you forever.

12:31.751 --> 12:34.413
Hey, when was the last time
you took a bath, huh?

12:34.587 --> 12:36.543
I can't live without you.

12:37.507 --> 12:40.089
I know we've been having problems,
but I got that figured out.

12:40.260 --> 12:42.876
Hoyt, I, uh....

12:43.346 --> 12:45.257
I wanna move out.

12:45.682 --> 12:47.343
You want us to get a new place?

12:47.517 --> 12:50.304
I think that's a great idea,
because we'd start over.

12:50.520 --> 12:51.885
No. Uh....

12:53.273 --> 12:54.934
I don't wanna live together anymore.

12:56.943 --> 12:59.685
Sorry, I'm not-- I'm not made for this.

12:59.862 --> 13:04.982
I have a hunger
in the very center of me...

13:05.159 --> 13:11.621
...and this, you and me, I can't--
It's not enough.

13:11.791 --> 13:17.627
I wish it was, because I love you and
I don't wanna hurt you, but it's not enough.

13:17.797 --> 13:19.879
It just isn't.

13:20.633 --> 13:21.668
I'm sorry.

13:24.053 --> 13:25.168
You don't mean that.

13:28.057 --> 13:29.763
Hoyt, I do.

13:30.184 --> 13:32.095
I really do. It's over.

13:32.270 --> 13:33.635
It's--

13:34.230 --> 13:35.891
[HOYT SOBBING]

13:36.065 --> 13:38.477
You're too good for me.

13:38.943 --> 13:40.808
I was too happy.

13:40.987 --> 13:43.694
I should have known
I could never be this happy.

13:44.866 --> 13:47.824
Of course you can be happy. You just--

13:47.994 --> 13:51.236
You aren't getting all of me
because of what I am, and you....

13:51.414 --> 13:54.998
-You deserve someone better than me.
-I don't want someone better than you.

13:55.168 --> 13:57.124
I want you.

13:57.420 --> 13:59.832
If I can't have you,
I don't want to be alive.

14:01.841 --> 14:02.876
I need to go.

14:05.511 --> 14:07.672
-Get out of my way.
-I will die without you.

14:07.847 --> 14:11.010
-My God, just listen to yourself.
-I'm sorry. I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

14:11.184 --> 14:14.051
And I'm sorry that I said
that your blood is shit. It's not.

14:14.228 --> 14:16.935
It's not, and I will drink it every day
if you want.

14:17.106 --> 14:18.767
But love me.

14:18.941 --> 14:22.775
Please, please, please love me.
If you don't love me, I will die.

14:22.945 --> 14:24.025
Then die!

14:29.702 --> 14:32.865
[BLUEGRASS MUSIC PLAYING
ON STEREO]

14:38.211 --> 14:40.042
God.

14:40.505 --> 14:44.544
You are so fucking hot
when you got blood all over you.

14:46.552 --> 14:47.883
Stop it.

14:50.390 --> 14:56.477
I want you to bite me
and fuck me at the same time.

14:56.646 --> 14:57.806
Right here.

14:58.689 --> 14:59.724
Okay.

14:59.899 --> 15:01.139
Yeah.

15:02.235 --> 15:03.975
Come to daddy.

15:04.153 --> 15:05.233
RITA:
Jessica ?

15:05.405 --> 15:06.861
Jessica.

15:10.660 --> 15:11.900
Yeah?

15:12.662 --> 15:16.780
I'm Rita. I'm a donor.
The king sent me down for you.

15:16.958 --> 15:19.415
Yeah, sure.

15:19.585 --> 15:21.086
Thank you.

15:34.684 --> 15:37.050
AN DY:
Dead vampire.

15:37.311 --> 15:39.518
Should I call the coroner or sanitation?

15:39.689 --> 15:42.431
Bet you it's gonna rain tonight.

15:42.608 --> 15:47.102
I can always feel it
where that panther tore my throat open.

15:51.784 --> 15:52.864
What up, Andy?

15:53.953 --> 15:56.945
-So you're back on the force now?
-Got here as fast as I could.

15:57.123 --> 16:00.365
-Rosie said there was a vampire suicide.
-Wasn't a suicide.

16:01.043 --> 16:04.126
-Yeah, I know that.
ANDY: No evidence.

16:04.297 --> 16:06.458
Searched her house, no note.

16:06.632 --> 16:08.088
Yeah, can you believe it?

16:08.259 --> 16:10.796
Beulah Carter was a goddamn vampire.

16:14.891 --> 16:16.301
[GRUNTING]

16:16.726 --> 16:19.138
Oh, no. Andy.

16:19.562 --> 16:21.598
Andy. Whoa.

16:23.149 --> 16:27.939
You serious? You would eat a pile
of dead vampire Beulah Carter?

16:28.112 --> 16:30.068
Off the ground?

16:32.492 --> 16:35.199
You are one sad, sorry freak, bubba.

16:35.369 --> 16:36.404
Get a fucking grip.

16:37.246 --> 16:39.828
Jesus, tits and God America, Jason.

16:39.999 --> 16:41.990
What the fuck is happening to me?

16:43.252 --> 16:45.413
I'm only good on the V, dude.

16:45.588 --> 16:48.204
It's the only time I feel
like I'm not watching myself...

16:48.382 --> 16:52.546
...not living up to people's expectations,
then hating them for having expectations...

16:52.762 --> 16:55.970
...then thinking about hitting
them in the head with a bat.

16:57.016 --> 16:59.678
Sorry, man. I stopped listening
about halfway through.

17:01.479 --> 17:04.596
THEA: So no one in the neighborhood
knew she was a vampire?

17:04.774 --> 17:07.686
I must say I did wonder about her.

17:07.860 --> 17:10.727
She kept to herself like a vampire would.

17:10.905 --> 17:13.942
-Or a serial killer.
-Ooh. Hm.

17:14.700 --> 17:18.739
MAXINE: That's the most famous vampire
in town right there.

17:18.913 --> 17:21.370
Wonder if he knew
she was one of his own.

17:22.041 --> 17:23.281
Mrs. Fortenberry.

17:23.876 --> 17:25.207
Vampire Bill.

17:26.546 --> 17:29.288
Did you know Beulah Carter
was a vampire?

17:30.007 --> 17:33.215
Because all of us vampires
know each other?

17:33.386 --> 17:35.342
Are vampire suicides common?

17:35.513 --> 17:37.378
Sadly, yes.

17:37.557 --> 17:41.391
Many vampires feel alone and confused...

17:41.561 --> 17:43.768
...programmed to despise themselves...

17:43.938 --> 17:49.399
...by all the hateful and incendiary
anti-vampire rhetoric in the media.

17:50.194 --> 17:52.731
That's good.
Can I get you to say that again?

17:52.905 --> 17:56.068
Of course.
I actually have a statement prepared.

17:58.578 --> 18:01.570
I am very telegenic.

18:02.081 --> 18:04.072
This will get a lot of play.

18:04.667 --> 18:08.000
It's an excellent opportunity
for you to impress your producers...

18:08.170 --> 18:10.422
...with your eye for great TV.

18:12.758 --> 18:17.252
Lenny, can we get
a really good tight shot of him...

18:17.430 --> 18:19.967
...and make sure
you really play up the eyes.

18:34.155 --> 18:36.521
It's a miracle.

18:37.783 --> 18:39.614
What is?

18:40.494 --> 18:42.450
You.

18:43.039 --> 18:45.121
Your blood.

18:46.459 --> 18:48.791
It's amazing.

18:49.670 --> 18:51.285
So is yours.

19:25.331 --> 19:27.663
It's snowing.

19:39.345 --> 19:41.927
Why is there a bed?

19:42.431 --> 19:44.547
Can we make love in it?

19:44.850 --> 19:47.683
Like, maybe never stop.

19:48.104 --> 19:50.846
-Why would we ever want to?
-Heh, heh.

19:51.565 --> 19:53.851
[BOTH LAUGHING]

20:31.647 --> 20:34.559
Bill, why would a vampire
commit suicide?

20:34.734 --> 20:40.946
Well, Thea, I can only guess
that the pervasive anti-vampire hatred...

20:41.115 --> 20:45.108
...that has persisted since the heinous
crime perpetrated by Russell Edgington...

20:45.286 --> 20:46.822
...had something to do with it.

20:49.039 --> 20:52.406
And that hate is a powerful force...

20:52.585 --> 20:54.792
...but hate never wins out.

20:55.004 --> 20:56.289
Not in the long run.

20:56.714 --> 21:00.172
And we will never succumb to it.
As Christ himself said. . ..

21:00.760 --> 21:02.751
Here, here. Let me-- Let me show you.

21:03.596 --> 21:05.427
So that is it?

21:08.100 --> 21:12.264
A single vampire dies four centuries ago.

21:12.438 --> 21:17.478
-AI| vampires within 20 miles burned.
-Wait a minute.

21:17.651 --> 21:19.812
You made that vampire go out
into the daylight.

21:20.029 --> 21:22.691
We did, Tara. We did.

21:22.865 --> 21:26.153
So we're notjust protecting ourselves,
we're killing vampires.

21:26.327 --> 21:29.535
Killing them is the only way
to protect ourselves.

21:30.790 --> 21:34.203
At least in my time,
they remained hidden.

21:34.376 --> 21:40.997
Now they walk among us,
shameless in their lust, their hunger.

21:41.175 --> 21:45.293
They laugh at the miracle of life.

21:45.596 --> 21:50.966
We must restore the sacred power
of creation to this wounded earth.

21:51.143 --> 21:53.304
That is our only hope.

21:53.479 --> 21:55.094
Snuff them out!

21:55.481 --> 21:56.971
Once and for all.

21:59.068 --> 22:00.808
Nothing would make me happier...

22:00.986 --> 22:03.819
...than to see those dead fucks
gone for good.

22:05.658 --> 22:07.649
I can empower you.

22:07.827 --> 22:10.819
I can teach you.

22:11.247 --> 22:13.533
[PHONE RINGING]

22:17.586 --> 22:18.996
Moongoddess Emporium.

22:19.171 --> 22:21.583
BILL: Tara?
-Uh-huh.

22:21.882 --> 22:24.419
-What are you doing there?
-What do you want, Bill?

22:25.845 --> 22:28.336
To speak to Antonia Gavilan de Logrono.

22:34.311 --> 22:37.178
-She's on.
-Lady Antonia.

22:39.233 --> 22:40.268
Vampire.

22:40.442 --> 22:43.525
On behalf of all vampires in Louisiana
and throughout the world...

22:43.696 --> 22:46.108
...I apologize for what was done to you.

22:46.532 --> 22:52.698
It was a crime of unspeakable magnitude
for which there can be no forgiveness.

22:53.706 --> 22:56.413
But there can, / believe,
be peace between us.

22:56.625 --> 22:58.286
Peace?

22:59.044 --> 23:00.375
What peace?

23:00.546 --> 23:04.255
One of you came here
to Marnie's place of worship.

23:04.425 --> 23:06.211
You molested her.

23:06.385 --> 23:09.218
-You bit her like an animal.
-I know.

23:09.889 --> 23:11.379
I sent him...

23:11.557 --> 23:13.798
...and it was a tragic mistake...

23:14.435 --> 23:16.175
...one I deeply regret.

23:16.353 --> 23:19.766
It was a mistake borne
out of arrogance...

23:20.900 --> 23:22.606
...and ignorance of who you were.

23:22.776 --> 23:25.904
It does not matter who I am.

23:26.071 --> 23:29.154
Every soul is entitled to live freely.

23:29.325 --> 23:32.158
You are an affront to God
when you deny that.

23:32.328 --> 23:36.116
I can only tell you that there are many
of us who believe as you do.

23:36.290 --> 23:38.781
And we wield considerable power
among our kind.

23:39.001 --> 23:40.081
ANTONIA:
Oh.

23:40.252 --> 23:41.412
[ANTONIA CHUCKLES]

23:41.587 --> 23:44.875
Oh, the rulers of vampires,
they are my allies?

23:45.049 --> 23:46.585
